01:30:20.920 --> 01:30:23.920
[Guest]: not even for a reason just because this person is a threat

01:30:23.920 --> 01:30:26.920
[Guest]: to my rule so I get him beheaded so this became the norm and

01:30:26.920 --> 01:30:29.920
[Guest]: you know people take a lot of umbrage over

01:30:29.920 --> 01:30:32.920
[Guest]: a woman ruler doing the same thing which a male ruler might get

01:30:32.920 --> 01:30:35.920
[Guest]: a pass for but then regardless of the gender

01:30:35.920 --> 01:30:38.920
[Guest]: she did do bad things later in her life

01:30:38.920 --> 01:30:41.920
[Guest]: as a queen because you know once power gets in your head

01:30:41.920 --> 01:30:44.920
[Guest]: so that's another lesson from history that history is

01:30:44.920 --> 01:30:47.920
[Guest]: not good versus evil it's not

01:30:47.920 --> 01:30:50.920
[Guest]: black and white you have good people doing bad things bad people

01:30:50.920 --> 01:30:53.920
[Guest]: doing good things it's like all

01:30:53.920 --> 01:30:56.920
[Guest]: over the place so Begum Samru had a very difficult

01:30:56.920 --> 01:30:59.920
[Guest]: life she is a story of courage and everything

01:30:59.920 --> 01:31:02.920
[Guest]: but later in her life she is a story of

01:31:02.920 --> 01:31:05.920
[Guest]: extreme despotism and

01:31:05.920 --> 01:31:08.920
[Guest]: you know much worse than what many people

01:31:08.920 --> 01:31:11.920
[Guest]: view of Modi as you know so

01:31:11.920 --> 01:31:14.920
[Guest]: these both sides exist

01:31:14.920 --> 01:31:17.920
[Amit Varma]: in the same person and the interesting thing is

01:31:17.920 --> 01:31:20.920
[Amit Varma]: just thinking aloud is that one of the problems

01:31:20.920 --> 01:31:23.920
[Amit Varma]: with history is that we make historical figures larger than life

01:31:23.920 --> 01:31:26.920
[Amit Varma]: so the good they do gets amplified in our minds

01:31:26.920 --> 01:31:29.920
[Amit Varma]: the bad they do gets amplified in our minds and when we want to take a position

01:31:29.920 --> 01:31:32.920
[Amit Varma]: that they're good or bad we obviously ignore the one and

01:31:32.920 --> 01:31:35.920
[Amit Varma]: focus on the other but it strikes me that

01:31:35.920 --> 01:31:38.920
[Amit Varma]: you know the human emotions that she must have gone through any historical

01:31:38.920 --> 01:31:41.920
[Amit Varma]: figure goes through you know there is the frustration there is suffering

01:31:41.920 --> 01:31:44.920
[Amit Varma]: anger there is then resentment some of that resentment

01:31:44.920 --> 01:31:47.920
[Amit Varma]: might play out later when she is beheading people who were

01:31:47.920 --> 01:31:50.920
[Amit Varma]: earlier among the people who oppressed her and so

01:31:50.920 --> 01:31:53.920
[Amit Varma]: on and so forth and all of these emotions are in play

01:31:53.920 --> 01:31:56.920
[Amit Varma]: and the only difference between us and them is those

01:31:56.920 --> 01:31:59.920
[Amit Varma]: specific circumstances that led to them doing

01:31:59.920 --> 01:32:02.920
[Guest]: whatever they are doing you know like I look at Gandhi's life

01:32:02.920 --> 01:32:05.920
[Amit Varma]: for example and Gandhi is really fascinating to me because

01:32:05.920 --> 01:32:08.920
[Amit Varma]: he is such a deeply flawed figure who happened to do great

01:32:08.920 --> 01:32:11.920
[Amit Varma]: things who in some ways you can admire him a lot

01:32:11.920 --> 01:32:14.920
[Amit Varma]: in some ways you just go like you know what the f**k is that

01:32:14.920 --> 01:32:17.920
[Amit Varma]: even especially his treatment of women and the stuff he did

01:32:17.920 --> 01:32:20.920
[Guest]: in the later years of his life, caste for that matter

01:32:20.920 --> 01:32:23.920
[Amit Varma]: and I always think that initially

01:32:23.920 --> 01:32:26.920
[Amit Varma]: he is trying to kind of play it

01:32:26.920 --> 01:32:29.920
[Amit Varma]: safe when he defends a Varna system and all that but

01:32:29.920 --> 01:32:32.920
[Amit Varma]: later when he claims to be against caste I think he is just virtue

01:32:32.920 --> 01:32:35.920
[Amit Varma]: signaling and which Ambedkar correctly saw which really

01:32:35.920 --> 01:32:38.920
[Amit Varma]: irritated Ambedkar because he is like what the f**k your virtue

01:32:38.920 --> 01:32:41.920
[Amit Varma]: signaling though not in so many words but you know in the

01:32:41.920 --> 01:32:44.920
[Amit Varma]: Twitter of those days that's exactly what he was doing and

01:32:44.920 --> 01:32:47.920
[Amit Varma]: Ambedkar you know could see through him and

01:32:47.920 --> 01:32:50.920
[Amit Varma]: in a sense in this particular debate Savarkar was in a sense

01:32:50.920 --> 01:32:53.920
[Amit Varma]: on Ambedkar's side in the caste debate which

01:32:53.920 --> 01:32:56.920
[Amit Varma]: people don't appreciate and we look at things like Gandhi's

01:32:56.920 --> 01:32:59.920
[Amit Varma]: racism against blacks in South Africa and he

01:32:59.920 --> 01:33:02.920
[Amit Varma]: changes his mind on that later and at every point you know

01:33:02.920 --> 01:33:05.920
[Amit Varma]: you come with your biases you respond to incentives you change with

01:33:05.920 --> 01:33:08.920
[Amit Varma]: times you even look at Savarkar's mercy petitions for example

01:33:08.920 --> 01:33:11.920
[Amit Varma]: I don't even see why they are a big deal the guy is dead

01:33:11.920 --> 01:33:14.920
[Amit Varma]: we should only you know debating his ideas is

01:33:14.920 --> 01:33:17.920
[Amit Varma]: enough his book Hindutva is like disgusting I had

01:33:17.920 --> 01:33:20.920
[Amit Varma]: to read it once for an episode I did with Akar Patel

01:33:20.920 --> 01:33:23.920
[Amit Varma]: it's a horrendously bad book and those ideas can be criticized

01:33:23.920 --> 01:33:26.920
[Amit Varma]: on their own you don't need a reference to his life

01:33:26.920 --> 01:33:29.920
[Amit Varma]: but the point is I don't blame him for writing those mercy petitions

01:33:29.920 --> 01:33:32.920
[Amit Varma]: because he was not being kept in a 5 star house like Nehru

01:33:32.920 --> 01:33:35.920
[Amit Varma]: and Gandhi were when they were imprisoned or when they were detained

01:33:35.920 --> 01:33:38.920
[Amit Varma]: by the British he was literally tortured you read the prison

01:33:38.920 --> 01:33:41.920
[Amit Varma]: diaries of the people in Andamas in those days it's kind of

01:33:41.920 --> 01:33:44.920
[Amit Varma]: terrible I don't know why it's become such a polarizing thing

01:33:44.920 --> 01:33:47.920
[Amit Varma]: I would write a letter like that just to actually maybe I wouldn't

01:33:47.920 --> 01:33:50.920
[Amit Varma]: but whatever it would be understandable if someone was to do that

01:33:50.920 --> 01:33:53.920
[Amit Varma]: in that particular circumstance and that has absolutely

01:33:53.920 --> 01:33:56.920
[Amit Varma]: no bearing on his ideas you know his ideas

01:33:56.920 --> 01:33:59.920
[Amit Varma]: and his actions can be judged by themselves

01:33:59.920 --> 01:34:02.920
[Amit Varma]: and what the person did in all the very complex things

01:34:02.920 --> 01:34:05.920
[Amit Varma]: that happened to him is really difficult to paint

01:34:05.920 --> 01:34:08.920
[Amit Varma]: in either black or white because hey we feel those same emotions

01:34:08.920 --> 01:34:12.920
[Amit Varma]: and do different crazy things at different times of our lives

01:34:12.920 --> 01:34:15.920
[Guest]: I mean the kind of times we are living in everyone

01:34:15.920 --> 01:34:18.920
[Guest]: we discussed that right that it's

01:34:18.920 --> 01:34:21.920
[Guest]: there is incentive in having opinions

01:34:21.920 --> 01:34:25.920
[Guest]: good or bad whatever it's a fear of missing out on a bus

01:34:25.920 --> 01:34:28.920
[Guest]: we have to have an opinion before the issue dies out

01:34:28.920 --> 01:34:31.920
[Guest]: and you give an opinion you will get a certain number of likes

01:34:31.920 --> 01:34:34.920
[Guest]: and retweets and you will be validated you will feel like a hero

01:34:34.920 --> 01:34:37.920
[Guest]: and fine then let the issue die

01:34:37.920 --> 01:34:40.920
[Guest]: today in India the conflict is not of

01:34:40.920 --> 01:34:43.920
[Guest]: ideologies that's what I believe

01:34:43.920 --> 01:34:46.920
[Guest]: the conflict is of attention

01:34:46.920 --> 01:34:49.920
[Guest]: who is getting the lion's share of attention so if

01:34:49.920 --> 01:34:52.920
[Guest]: by bringing out Savarkar's mercy petition

01:34:52.920 --> 01:34:55.920
[Guest]: I can get the attention fine I'll do it

01:34:55.920 --> 01:34:58.920
[Guest]: if bringing up Savarkar being a good guy

01:34:58.920 --> 01:35:01.920
[Guest]: and stuff you know Gandhi having a

01:35:01.920 --> 01:35:04.920
[Guest]: hand in whatever flaws you find in Savarkar

01:35:04.920 --> 01:35:07.920
[Guest]: Gandhi having a hand in that if bringing that

01:35:07.920 --> 01:35:10.920
[Guest]: out gets me a book deal and gets me you know

01:35:10.920 --> 01:35:13.920
[Guest]: it's a Hindutva nation right now for all practical

01:35:13.920 --> 01:35:16.920
[Guest]: purposes it's a Saffron nation and in a Saffron nation

01:35:16.920 --> 01:35:19.920
[Guest]: if that narrative works and gets me a book deal and gets me

01:35:19.920 --> 01:35:22.920
[Guest]: a lot of popularity why not and so

01:35:22.920 --> 01:35:25.920
[Guest]: everyone is about their own personal agenda

01:35:25.920 --> 01:35:28.920
[Guest]: not even ideological agenda it's a personal agenda

01:35:28.920 --> 01:35:31.920
[Guest]: and this is not pointing finger at anyone

01:35:31.920 --> 01:35:34.920
[Guest]: in particular now my only question is

01:35:34.920 --> 01:35:37.920
[Guest]: if I would I talk about

01:35:37.920 --> 01:35:40.920
[Guest]: Savarkar and call out his mercy petition

01:35:40.920 --> 01:35:43.920
[Guest]: as a desperate move will I criticize it

01:35:43.920 --> 01:35:46.920
[Guest]: but then before I do that

01:35:46.920 --> 01:35:49.920
[Guest]: I would like to put myself in those shoes and

