03:02:19.920 --> 03:02:22.920
[Amit Varma]: and I remember Sawati Banerjee this journalist

03:02:22.920 --> 03:02:25.920
[Amit Varma]: based then in Delhi I think did a very interesting piece

03:02:25.920 --> 03:02:28.920
[Amit Varma]: and I think there is a video of it somewhere I will look for it if I can find it

03:02:28.920 --> 03:02:31.920
[Amit Varma]: where she tried to imagine what an Indus Valley dish

03:02:31.920 --> 03:02:34.920
[Amit Varma]: might have been like if I remember correctly some prehistoric dish

03:02:34.920 --> 03:02:37.920
[Amit Varma]: before all of this foreign stuff came in

03:02:37.920 --> 03:02:40.920
[Amit Varma]: she concluded if I remember correctly that there was

03:02:40.920 --> 03:02:43.920
[Amit Varma]: brinjal in it but I don't remember any other part of it

03:02:43.920 --> 03:02:46.920
[Guest]: brinjal, mustard

